[thinking] **Inspecting native reflection**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm thinking about how native reflection requires something to be registered, yet the JDK might still be reachable. If the private constructor test has no config, it seems that native methods fail due to missing reflection metadata. However, I'm wondering if the test will generate metadata itself. It looks like the user-code-filter excludes everything but includes org.springframework, so it probably records library details. I should check the metadata repository for Spring's reflect utilities to see if the metadata collection is broad enough.
