e a few potential issues to address, especially with NativeImageSupport imports and CodeGenerationException errors.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Addressing fallback and class loading issues**\\n\\nI'm looking into a potential issue with the fallback mechanism for tests on JVM JDK 21. It seems that when `classLoaderDefineClassMethod.setAccessible(true)` throws an InaccessibleObjectException, I need to handle that. If `classLoaderDefineClassMethod` is null due to a static initializer catching a Throwable, the declared method doesn't set accessible, which might not throw. There's also a situation where the context class loader's lookup may conflict if packages match. It's important to ensure that class definitions and initializations are handled correctly across different loaders to avoid conflicts.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring class definition and method issues**\\n\\nI'm examining whether defining a class with the same package in a child class loader when the parent has sealed might present issues. It seems that `Class.getMethod` only retrieves public methods, and the ClassLoader subclass needs to be public as well. Also, I'm considering the potential issue with generated class names that use an Atomic sequence, but I'm relieved that each test runs in a fresh native context. It helps keep things isolated and avoids conflicts.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_pe3vk81griSM9IgPySnS4fGv|fc_026533928cd3cd210169f5894cfcc881a0948c061a2a4f79ad", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge8/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.springframework/spring-core/5.3.15/main/extracted/org/springframework/core/Ordered.java", "limit": 120}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2024, "output": 974, "cacheRead": 40448, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 43446, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}